      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "content: '# Web Document\n\n\n  ## Metadata\n\n\n  - title: Chase Debit/ATM Card | Frequently Asked Questions | Chase\n\n  - url: https://www.chase.com/personal/personal-account/faqs/debit-atm-card\n\n  - source: Chase\n\n  - domain: chase.com\n\n\n  ## Content\n\n\n  # Chase debit/ATM card FAQs\n\n\n  This Chase help page answers common questions about Chase debit and ATM cards, including\n  card arrival, card activation, and options to lock or unlock a debit card.\n\n\n  ## When will my debit/ATM card arrive?\n\n\n  A debit or ATM card usually arrives about a week after a new account is opened.\n  If a card does not arrive within two weeks, the customer can request a new card\n  online. In the Chase Mobile app, customers can select the account and choose the\n  option to replace a lost or damaged card in the Manage account section.\n\n\n  ## How do I activate a debit card or ATM card?\n\n\n  A Chase debit card can be activated online, by calling 1-800-290-3935, or by completing\n  a transaction at a Chase ATM using the card PIN. An ATM card can be used immediately.\n\n\n  ## How can I lock or unlock my debit card if it is lost or misplaced?\n\n\n  Chase lists two account-based ways to lock or unlock a debit card:\n\n\n  1. In the Chase Mobile app, choose the account to lock or unlock. Select **Manage\n  account**, select **Lock & unlock card**, and follow the prompts.\n\n  2. On chase.com, sign in, choose the account, select **More**, open the **Account\n  services** dropdown, select **Lock and unlock your card**, and follow the prompts.\n\n  '\nmetadata: {}\ntitle: Chase Debit/ATM Card | Frequently Asked Questions | Chase\nurl: https://www.chase.com/personal/personal-account/faqs/debit-atm-card"
        }
      ],
