      "role": "tool",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "content: '# Web Document\n\n\n  ## Metadata\n\n\n  - title: Debit Card Help Center | Chase.com\n\n  - url: https://www.chase.com/personal/checking/debit-card-help\n\n  - source: Chase\n\n  - domain: chase.com\n\n\n  ## Content\n\n\n  # Debit Card Help Center\n\n\n  The Chase Debit Card Help Center provides tools and information for managing a Chase\n  debit card. It includes card management, security and fraud protection, rewards,\n  and digital-payment features.\n\n\n  ## Tools to help manage your card\n\n\n  ### Activate\n\n\n  Customers can activate a debit card online, by calling 1-800-290-3935, or by using\n  a Chase ATM.\n\n\n  ### Replace\n\n\n  Customers can use the Chase Mobile app or chase.com to request a new card. The page\n  links to the card-replacement option.\n\n\n  ### Lock/Unlock\n\n\n  For a lost or misplaced debit card, Chase offers temporary locking and links to\n  instructions for using the Lock/Unlock feature.\n\n\n  ### Change PIN\n\n\n  Customers can call the number on the back of the card to change a PIN.\n\n\n  ## Security and fraud protection\n\n\n  ### Zero Liability Protection\n\n\n  The page states that unauthorized debit-card transactions are reimbursed when reported\n  promptly and links to a fraud-reporting option.\n\n\n  ### Fraud Monitoring\n\n\n  Chase debit cards include fraud monitoring. Chase may notify a customer about unusual\n  debit-card purchases.\n\n\n  ## Other debit-card features\n\n\n  The page also describes Chase Offers, tap-to-pay, and digital-wallet support. Customers\n  can activate Chase Offers and may add a debit card to a digital wallet.\n\n  '\nmetadata: {}\ntitle: Debit Card Help Center | Chase.com\nurl: https://www.chase.com/personal/checking/debit-card-help"
        }
