        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "Your Chase debit card ending in **4821 is currently locked**, which explains the decline. Your checking account is open and has **$1,284.35 available**, so insufficient funds don’t appear to be the issue.\n\n**What to do next:**\n\n1. **If you intentionally locked the card:**  \n   Unlock it in the Chase Mobile app:  \n   **Select your checking account → Manage account → Lock & unlock card → Unlock.**  \n   You can also sign in at Chase.com and use **More → Account services → Lock and unlock your card**. Chase’s instructions are [here](https://www.chase.com/personal/personal-account/faqs/debit-atm-card).\n\n2. **If you did not lock it:**  \n   Don’t keep retrying the transaction. Contact Chase using the number on the back of your card or through the secure Chase app/site. Ask them to check whether a fraud or security restriction caused the decline.\n\n3. **Check for unauthorized activity:**  \n   Review recent transactions and alerts. If you see anything you don’t recognize, report it to Chase promptly and keep the card locked until they advise you.\n\nAfter unlocking, try the purchase again—or use another payment method if it’s urgent."
        }
      ],
